content.description: Figure out a way to balance your way up the slab in order to get to the left facing crimp in the crack.  Make a dynamic move to a big hold and then top out.
content.location: Take the trail that is directly behind the restrooms at the second to last parking lot at the North Shore.  Show me the kind is at the top of the hill on the right.

content.description: Tricky.  Climb up on thin holds to the top.  Avoid the left arete.
content.location: Boulder just right of Show Me the Kind.

content.description: Same face as Show Me the Kind, but uses large sloper right hand just over the roof and over to the right.  Also can use the big foot over to the right.
content.location: Show Me The Kind boulder, uses holds eliminated from that problem.

content.description: Fun arete, kind of tricky with squeezy balancy moves.  Super satisfying topout.
content.location: Arete left of Show Me the Kind.

climbs.name: The Power of The Chrome Dome

content.description: Climb up boulder just right of corner and Giese Dome.  Avoid the crack on right.
content.location: Same directions as The Giese Dome.

climbs.name: Invisibility Cloak
climbs.fa: Ian CB or Old school? Coulda been top rope too?

content.description: Start from a stand, right hand up high on an okay shelf and left on an undercling. Pull on and launch up the intimidating and airy arête, probably moving slightly right on good holds and feet for the finish. The walls, detached blocks, trees or whatever aren't used, climb the arête!
content.location: Just below Show Me the Kind.  A minute walk straight above the bathroom from the parking lot.

content.description: Climb up featured lay-back just left of Giese Dome.
content.location: Featured face left of Giese Dome.

content.description: Start just left of corner, crank up to a good ledge and slopey topout.  Really fun V2, a must do.
content.location: Hike on East Bluff trail past Show me the Kind about 50 yrds and cut towards the lake.  You should see a small trail that leads you to this boulder.

content.description: Start on large rail and make some fun moves up the arete. Watch out for the wall on the left, dab potential.
Not far from the high concentration of problems on the North Shore, the Show Me The Kind area provides even more easy problems, in addition to a few moderate to hard climbs.
